		<descript>
			<langdata>eng</langdata>
			<abstract>This is a scanned version of the  paper map entitled: The Conquered Provinces on the South of Bahar: Containing Ramgur, Palamow &amp; Chuta-Nagpour with Their Dependencies.  The map was scanned at 300 dots per inch and is in the TIFF format. Thanks to Prof. Frances Pritchett, Columbia University, for providing the original paper map for this scan.</abstract>
			<purpose>Scanned maps may be used for a variety of purposes.   This image may be used in a GIS; the dataset includes a .txt file containing a table of coordinates that may be used to aid in georeferencing the image; to use the coordinate table make sure that the data frame is in the WGS 1984 projection, then open the link table from the georeferencing toolbar, then select the load button, then navigate to the accompanying LINKTABLE.txt file.</purpose>
<supplinf>1 mapa grab., col. 42 x 39 cm en h. de 54 x 48 cm.
 Escala [ca. 1:757.300]. 40 British Miles [= 8,5]
Behar. S. (India) (Provincia) Mapas generales 1779.; Behar. S. (India) (Provincia); Divisiones administrativas; 1779.
Inscribed to Major Jacob Camac by his most obedt. Servant J. Rennell ; W. Harrison sc.</supplinf>
		</descript>
